content: This is just to get your attention. Not sure why, but the game did not work right, some things would not trigger after certain events and the renters website was completely down, 401 error... I am not disappointed the story line was great, but people are paying real money for this...
Its an okay game. I do wish that you teach the new users how to play with a tutorial. I already understand alittle.
I payed it a long time ago and now it was FREE!? ARE YOU KIDDING ME I WANT MY MONEY BACKüò†

This was a lot of fun! The story kept me engaged, and I really enjoyed puzzle solving with cmd prompts. My only two issues with the game were that 1) I couldn't turn the vibration off my phone. It's cool for suspenseful parts, but not when playing out in public places. The settings tab also wasn't accessible. Issue 2) is that some of the prompts weren't given ahead of time. 'get', 'move', etc, so I had no clue what to do other than use the answer key to move ahead. Fun game otherwise‚ÄîWaiting for Part 3!
How nice and coool!!! I've played first vesion. And also, i'm playing this now!! So brilliant!!
Was really fun while it lasted. I finished within a day...
Third one please?
When are the third and fourth games going to be available on Android?
Would not let me run the maim command in the end. Why?

Played to the first Hack Run, now this one, and surely hope there will be another one. Just love it ! Challenging, even if the answer isn't always obvious. Great game with a intriguing, bizarre, and sometimes funny storyline. Great job and keep up the good work !
Finished the first one in one night... This one had more content despite a lot of repetition. Awesome game and would buy the next one.
More please!!!!!!

**SPOILER ALERT** I used the answer cmd so many times because I can't guess things that are simply not known and have to be guessed. Eg. 'core' and 'deac' -no unix system I've used does deac deactivate things, which is fine if you don't have to guess it - kinda silly way to make things abstruse. Systems come with instructions, man. Why are the full set of runtime commands hidden (from the head of IT)? Ohhh, because you couldn't think of any more ways to make the game harder, and expanding on terminal commands was too much work. The other Hack Run was a bit repetitive, with the constant passwd hunt...but it was more natural to play. This version is irrational.
I love these hack games more please
This has everything I look for in a game. Puzzles, excitement, well developed and interesting. An excellent idea for a game in a new format. I need more!
When is the next game coming out?
Can't wait for the next one!!
Some of the puzzles were kind of oblique this time. Still a great concept. Hopefully the next one adds functional bookmarks instead of just the one. That was an awful tease.
THIS GAME IS AWESOME!!!

Loved the first one. Can't wait to play this one........beat it loved it but one thing I might add is that some parts make no sense in the story line but it was still a great game I look foreward to more adventures
